Nigeria, on Tuesday night, defeated Ecuador 3-2 to qualify for the round of 16, at the ongoing FIFA U-17 World Cup in Brazil. The Golden Eaglets had produced a thrilling display, to see off Hungary 4-2 in their opening fixture. Ibrahim Said scored all three goals, as Manu Garba’s men showed resilience to beat Ecuador. The victory extended Nigeria’s dominance at the top of Group B to six points after two matches. They will be looking to end their group campaign on a high, when they battle Australia on Friday. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.